track_notes: Park neatly in the entrance to the track, plenty of room for 1 car to park without blocking access. Limited ground clearance for low cars. Follow forestry tracks to emerge onto the hillside. Continue up alongside a stream until you reach the col (boggy in parts). See Glascwm to take in that summit. If just heading to Aran Fawddwy turn left (NE) at the col and follow path and duck boards in places across the flatter section, before climbing to the summit. Ignore initial false summit (870m) and continue to the main summit some 400m further on.

Total time (including ops): 5hr 25m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Aran Fawddwy and Glasgwm Linear from Rhydymain. Dec 2019.

track_notes:
Park at Cwm Cywarch CP ( SH852188 / N52:45:18 W3:42:06). Room for 10+ cars and has toilet facility.
Leave CP heading South. After 100m cross the bridge on LHS and follow the path up towards Drysgol. Pass the monument and Head E, NW and then NE at the boundary to the Aran Fawddwy summit.
Retrace your steps and continue to head SW to descent along the boundary.
Cross the wet boggy area and ascent with the boundary on your left to reach Glasgwm.
Pass the tarn and head South with the boundary on your RHS until you reach the service track.
Turn left when reaching the road to head back to the CP.

Total ascent: 1,208m

(This route is the reverse of the one posted on the Glasgwm page).
track_title: Aran Fawddwy to Glasgwm circular from Cwm Cywarch CP Apr 2022

track_notes:
Parking in National Park car park next to bus turning area.

Head back towards village and take sigposted footpath,  follow along side of field then turn left at the corner of the field and head uphill to road/track.  Turn right onto bridleway and follow signs for ridge path which bears left after 500m on the bridleway.  Follow path to summit. 

Path is mostly straightforward but several false summits en route.  One short section of scree on my route but it looked like you can go around this,  and the final climb is straightforward on a narrow path but might require putting a hand or two down.

Route done as ascent only and I continued on to Glasgwm then down to Rhydymain (T3 bus back to car).
